# ocean-science local configuration

Copy this file to your project as `ocean-science.local.md` and fill it in.
Skills read it at the start of ocean work; it never enters version control
if it contains paths you consider private. Filled with working defaults in
Session 10; template authored in Session 1 per SPECIFICATION.md v0.5.1 §4.1.

## Data locations

- ECCO release: v4r4
- ECCO local data directory: /path/to/ECCO_V4r4
- Download scratch directory (volume-gated loads land here): /path/to/scratch
- Maximum ungated download size: 2 GB (loaders ask before exceeding this)

## Compute

- Default compute label: small (laptop) | medium (Dask cluster) | large (HPC/burst)
- Dask: local cluster, n_workers = 4

## SWOT block

- Region of interest: lon [min, max], lat [min, max]
- Orbit phase default: 21-day science (set 1-day cal/val explicitly when intended;
  the swot-calval-orbit-phases gotcha applies to ranges spanning the switch)
- Product tier default: Expert
- Processing baseline: consult knowledge/datasets/swot-karin.md, do not hardcode here

## Knowledge block

- Installed standalone bundles consulted alongside this plugin's snapshot
  (SPEC §5.7), one path per line:
  - (none)
- Precedence reminder: provider-bundle concepts win on conflict.

## Earthdata Login

Credentials live in ~/.netrc (machine urs.earthdata.nasa.gov, chmod 600),
never in this file and never in any repo (SPEC §5.8).
